Ingredients

Flour 3 dl
Baking Powder 1 tsp
Salt 1 tsp
Butter (optional) 1 tbsp
Pig Fat (optional) 1 tbsp
Water 1.5 dl
Oil (optional) 1 tbsp

Instructions

Mix flour, baking powder, salt. 
Carefully melt butter OR pig fat. Mix together.
Add cold water. Knead together by hand or with a mixer for 5 minutes.
Add oil. Continue kneading for 5 more minutes.
Divide into small portions and roll into balls. Cover with plastic wrap. Rest for 30-60min.

Roll balls into tortillas with rolling pin or tortilla press or heavy object. Heat cast iron pan screaming hot.
Cook 20-30 seconds per side until small brown spots appear.
